ACF de modelos AR

AR(1)

rm(list=ls(all=TRUE))
set.seed(123)

# SimulaciÃ³n AR(1)
xt <- arima.sim(list(ar = c(0.79)), n = 1000)
ts.plot(xt)
acf(xt)  # Decae de forma exponencial

AR(2)

# SimulaciÃ³n AR(2) con coeficientes 0.8 y -0.55
xt2 <- arima.sim(list(order = c(2,0,0), ar = c(0.8, -0.55)), n = 1000)
ts.plot(xt2)
acf(xt2)

AR(2) no estacionario (Diapositiva 52)

# SimulaciÃ³n AR(2) con coeficientes 1.5 y -0.75
xt3 <- arima.sim(list(order = c(2,0,0), ar = c(1.5, -0.75)), n = 1000)
ts.plot(xt3)
acf(xt3)  # Decae de forma sinusoidal

## ACF de modelos AR

### AR(1)

```{r, fig.width=20, fig.height=5, out.width="100%"}
rm(list=ls(all=TRUE))
set.seed(123)

# SimulaciÃ³n AR(1)
xt <- arima.sim(list(ar = c(0.79)), n = 1000)
ts.plot(xt)
acf(xt)  # Decae de forma exponencial
```

### AR(2)

```{r, fig.width=20, fig.height=5, out.width="100%"}
# SimulaciÃ³n AR(2) con coeficientes 0.8 y -0.55
xt2 <- arima.sim(list(order = c(2,0,0), ar = c(0.8, -0.55)), n = 1000)
ts.plot(xt2)
acf(xt2)
```

### AR(2) no estacionario (Diapositiva 52)

```{r, fig.width=20, fig.height=5, out.width="100%"}
# SimulaciÃ³n AR(2) con coeficientes 1.5 y -0.75
xt3 <- arima.sim(list(order = c(2,0,0), ar = c(1.5, -0.75)), n = 1000)
ts.plot(xt3)
acf(xt3)  # Decae de forma sinusoidal
```

## PACF de modelos AR

### AR(1)

```{r, fig.width=20, fig.height=5, out.width="100%"}

ts.plot(xt)
par(mfrow = c(1,2))
acf(xt)
pacf(xt)
```

## Ejemplos adicionales con desviaciÃ³n estÃ¡ndar distinta

```{r, fig.width=20, fig.height=5, out.width="100%"}
# AR(2) con sd = 1.5
xt2 <- arima.sim(list(order = c(2,0,0), ar = c(0.2, 0.55)), sd = 1.5, n = 1000)

# MA(3) con sd = 3
yt3 <- arima.sim(list(ma = c(0.9, -0.8, -0.8)), sd = 3, n = 1000)
par(mfrow = c(1,2))
acf(yt3)
pacf(yt3)
```
